s-nobody-will-be-able-to-afford-to-make-music-if-monstrously-arrogant-tech-companies-continue-under-uk-governments-ai-copyright-rules-3841766">女王的布莱恩·梅（Brian May）谈到了政府的主张</a>，并告诉《 <a href="https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-14427469/Copyright-sell-silence-British-musicians-says-BRIAN-MAY.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>每日邮报》</em></a> ：“我担心它已经为时已晚 - 这种盗窃已经进行了，并且不可阻挡，就像许多入侵一样，AL和社交媒体的巨大亿万富翁所有者和社交媒体都在融入我们的生活。未来已经永远改变了。”</p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/paul-mccartney">保罗·麦卡特尼（Paul McCartney）</a>还<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/paul-mccartney-says-proposed-ai-copyright-law-will-rip-off-artists-3831960">批评了拟议的变化，说如果继续进行，它将允许AI撕毁艺术家，并导致“创造力丧失”</a> 。</p><p>同样， <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/Led-Zeppelin">LED Zeppelin</a>的<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/Jimmy-Page">Jimmy Page</a> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/led-zeppelins-jimmy-page-attacks-uk-governments-ai-copyright-plan-will-we-let-the-machines-take-the-stage-or-will-we-fight-for-the-irreplaceable-magic-of-human-artistry-3843158">对这些提案进行了反对</a>，他说：“当AI刮擦人类创造力的巨大挂毯以产生内容时，它通常在未经同意，归因或补偿的情况下进行。这不是创新；这是剥削。”</p><p>在其他地方，包括<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/damon-albarn">达蒙·阿尔巴恩（Damon Albarn）</a> ，<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/kate-bush">凯特·布什（Kate Bush）</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/annie-lennox">安妮·伦诺克斯（Annie Lennox）</a>在内的1,000多名艺术家发行了一张<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/damon-albarn-kate-bush-annie-lennox-over-1000-artists-release-silent-album-protest-uk-copyright-ai-laws-3841081">无声的专辑，以抗议英国政府计划的版权AI法律的计划更改</a>。 </p><figure id="attachment_3800034" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3800034" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3800034" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/celine-dion@2000x1270.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/celine-dion@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/up